line_1: My Closet not with Books, but Sweat-meats cram'd
line_2: Mysteries must not be, with my search Prophan'd,

line_1: Deceits through all her Letters cram'd,
line_2: The Oaths and Vows, and all the Dam'd,

line_1: His dying Epilogue with Curses cramm'd,
line_2: Has both the Arthurs, and their Author damn'd.

line_1: Though but an hour ago their throats they cramm'd,
line_2: And chirp'd, and cheep'd, and well the mother shamm'd.

line_1: O'th' stuff with which some folks are cram'd,
line_2: There yet are hopes he may'nt be damn'd.
